- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a graph colouring problem and involves proving NP-hardness and polynomial solvability results. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as planar graphs are mentioned and the paper deals with the complexity of colouring them. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper involves algorithmic complexity analysis and constructing polynomial time algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper deals with proving NP-hardness results. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with graph colouring, which is a topic of interest in game theory.
